description: CSharp toolkit containing useful extensions and functions.
releaseNotes:
New Additions:
      1. Validation Methods:
      ValidateNumBetweenCertainCharLength - The following method is designed in order to validate a number (represented in a string format) using the regular expression with a specified length. Example: Validate whether a string has a proper format (IE: 0-9) where the string has n numbers.
      2. ValidateFullName
      The following method is designed in order to validate a string containing full name. The validation is done using regular expression.
      3. ValidateEmailAddress
      The following method is designed in order to validate an email address represented in a string format. The validation process forcuses on the formation of the email and not whether an email address is deliverable.
      4. ValidateAlphaNumeric
      The following methid is designed in order to validate a string for alpha numeric.
